Go Commands:

Mac OS X package installer

Download the package file, open it, and follow the prompts to install the Go tools.
The package installs the Go distribution to /usr/local/go.

The package should put the /usr/local/go/bin directory in your PATH environment variable.
You may need to restart any open Terminal sessions for the change to take effect.

Intial steps
----------------

1. Install GO tools
2. Create a src dir: /Users/subbu/GO-Programming/src
3. Create a hello directory under src such that: 
Subbus-MacBook-Pro:hello subbu$ ls
hello.go
Subbus-MacBook-Pro:hello subbu$ pwd 
/Users/subbu/GO-Programming/src/hello

4.Set GOPATH variable
export GOPATH=/Users/subbu/GO-Programming

5.Run GO
go install hello

6.$ $GOPATH/bin/hello
hello, world

Optional to set, if not set: 
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin 


Alternate
---------

If you do not want to do all that, then:
Subbus-MacBook-Pro:hello subbu$ go run hello.go 
hello, world
Subbus-MacBook-Pro:hello subbu$ 


Alternate
----------
Subbus-MacBook-Pro:hello subbu$ go build hello.go 
Subbus-MacBook-Pro:hello subbu$ ./hello 
hello, world
Subbus-MacBook-Pro:hello subbu$ 




